<MainLayout>
    <h1>Digital Folder API Documentation</h1>
    
    ## POST - Digital Folder
    **URL**: `https://app.firmeasy.legal/api/v1/digital/carpeta`  
    **Description**: This endpoint is used to create a new digital folder.

    ## Request Body
    - `nombre` (string, required): The name of the new folder.
    - `descripcion` (string, optional): The description of the new folder.

    ### Example
    <pre class="astro-code bg-slate-800 text-white">
    {"{"}
        "nombre": "Carpeta Nueva"
    {"}"}
    </pre>

    ## Example Request (cURL)
    <pre class="astro-code bg-slate-800 text-white">
    curl --location 'https://app.firmeasy.legal/api/v1/digital/carpeta' \\
    --header 'Content-Type: application/json' \\
    --data '{"{"}
        "nombre": "Carpeta Nueva"
    {"}"}'
    </pre>

    ## Response
    The response of this request is a JSON schema.

    ### Example Response
    <pre class="astro-code bg-slate-800 text-white">
    {"{"}
        "success": true,
        "carpeta_id": "3b9266a1-2f13-5980-85c4-14edaa84a4d6",
        "message": "La Carpeta se cre√≥ satisfactoriamente"
    {"}"}
    </pre>

    ### JSON Schema
    <pre class="astro-code bg-slate-800 text-white">
    {"{"}
        "success": "boolean",
        "carpeta_id": "string",
        "message": "string"
    {"}"}
    </pre>

    ## Authorization
    **Bearer Token**: This request requires a Bearer Token from the Firmeasy API Production collection.

    ## Headers
    - `Content-Type`: `application/json`

    ## Request Body (Raw Format)
    <pre class="astro-code bg-slate-800 text-white">
    {"{"}
        "nombre": "Carpeta Nueva"
    {"}"}
    </pre>
</MainLayout>
